List of tags
============

Descriptions of section entries
-------------------------------

	D: *Description* of the tag
	S: *Sub-tag* list

General Purpose Tags List
-------------------------

build
D:	Build system

scripts
D:	Scripts used during development or build processes
S:	gencmd
	gencst

docs
D:	Documentations

vscode
D:	VS Code settings

cleanup
D:	Code cleanup

arch
D:	Architecture-specific implementations
S:	x86
	arm64
	riscv
	generic

cmd
D:	Commands
S:	backup
	copy
	help
	version
	....(same as the command name)

i18n
D:	Internationalization functionality

termas
D:	Terminal message handling

.....
There are many tags beyond the ones listed earlier. In general, each tag
corresponds to a header basename. You can find them under include/.

Per-platform Tags List
----------------------

.. note:: When using these tags, the tag itself should be prefixed by the
	  platform name (e.g., linux/acpy, windows/baksched)
	  The current available platform:

	  	linux
	  	windows

fcpy
D:	File copy handling

acpy
D:	Asynchronous file copy handling

fiter
D:	File iterator

bak
D:	Backup scheduler

dir
D:	Directory operations

path
D:	Pathname retrieving

proc
D:	Process handling

resc
D:	Resource querying

verc
D:	Version check

posix
D:	patch for POSIX function support
S:	<func-name>

----
rev 0.1
